history.content:
Your schedule/info provided doesn't leave a lot for people to work with.  However, for EECS related courses, there's not much else you can take, given that you have not completed 61B.  If you haven't taken EE16A/B, those are fine as well, because you will need to take them at some point.  If you have finished EE16 requirement, then the main upper div that makes sense would be EECS 126.  Other classes I think would build more upon CS61B and 61C, which you haven't taken.

Otherwise, always fine to take any other Math classes, etc.  or breadths if necessary.

I am currently auditing CS 61BL (finish all the labs, quizzes and exams) and I plan to take CS 61B next semester. I took CS 61A last fall and CS 70 last spring. Can anyone please comment on Hilfinger's CS 61B difficult and workload? Also, it there any class that are recommended to take concurrently with CS 61B next semester? (I'll have the knowledge of CS 61BL)
history.subject: Class to take with CS 61B?
